What is the output of the following code?

public static void tryToModify(String s) {
    s = s.toUpperCase();
}

String greeting = "hello";
tryToModify(greeting);
System.out.println(greeting);

What is the result of calling this method?

public static boolean isEven(int n) {
    return n % 2 == 0;
}

System.out.println(isEven(7));

Given these methods, what does isAlphanumeric('A') return?

public static boolean isLetter(char c) { return (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z'); }
public static boolean isDigit(char c) { return c >= '0' && c <= '9'; }
public static boolean isAlphanumeric(char c) { return isLetter(c) || isDigit(c); }

What will the following method return when called as factorial(5)?

public static long factorial(int n) {
    long result = 1;
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        result *= i;
    }
    return result;
}

What does the following code print?

public static void doubleAll(int[] arr) {
    for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        arr[i] *= 2;
    }
}

int[] nums = {1, 2, 3};
doubleAll(nums);
System.out.println(nums[0]);

